The Institute of Health Insurance conducts research to discover the gene responsible for the obesity of children and adolescents. Research is carried out with support from IPN experts
The Mexican Institute of Health Insurance (IMSS) announced that he was conducting research to detect a gene causing obesity in children and young people. The research called "Genetics of obesity in children and adolescents" will allow for overweight results.
In the report, Head of Biochemistry Medical Unit of the International Hospital of the National Health Centre of the 21st century, Miguel Cruz López, explained that a multidisciplinary team composed of doctors, sisters, nutrition experts and social workers was established.
This team is based on support for specialists and students of postgraduate studies from the National Institute of Public Health (INSP) and from the Research Centre and Advanced Studies (Cinvestav) of the National Polytechnic Institute (IPN).
Involved in research, a wide public with or without permission can also be involved. People can come to IMSS sports centres in Valle de México, where every sobor has been conducted since 8 hours by juvenile tests.
